    "summary": "Canvas Medical exposes a tenant-hosted FHIR R4 HTTP API plus a Python-based `canvas` CLI for plugin/application deployment and management; both use Canvas-issued OAuth credentials.",
    "description": "Canvas Medical provides an electronic medical record and care delivery platform for healthcare organizations. It supports workflow customization through plugins, applications, and API-based access to EHR data.",
    "credentials": {
      "canvas_oauth_cc": {
        "type": "oauth2_cc",
        "label": "Canvas OAuth client credentials app",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.canvasmedical.com/api/customer-authentication/",
        "setup": "In your Canvas instance, sign in as an administrator and create an OAuth application under `Settings > Integrations > OAuth Applications`. For CLI/server-to-server access, choose client type `confidential` and authorization grant type `client-credentials`, then save and copy the `client_id` and `client_secret`. The CLI guide says this is the same registration flow documented in [Customer Authentication](https://docs.canvasmedical.com/api/customer-authentication/) and used in [Your First Plugin (Manual)](https://docs.canvasmedical.com/guides/your-first-plugin/)."
      },
      "canvas_oauth_public": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Canvas OAuth public app (authorization code with PKCE)",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.canvasmedical.com/guides/note-management-oauth/",
        "setup": "In your Canvas instance, sign in as an administrator and go to `Settings > Integrations > OAuth Applications`, then create an application with client type `Public` and authorization grant type `Authorization Code`. Add your redirect URI, add the `offline_access` scope if you need refresh tokens, save, and copy the `client_id`. The setup is documented in [Note Management with External Applications](https://docs.canvasmedical.com/guides/note-management-oauth/)."
      }
    },
